# Entra ID app registration (single-tenant, registered in the Kemyion tenant).
# TWO redirect URIs are required — upstream's .env.example says to register the bare domain,
# which is wrong and fails with a redirect mismatch:
#   https://intuneget.app.vanheerden.ch/redirect                 (SPA)  — MSAL sign-in
#   https://intuneget.app.vanheerden.ch/auth/consent-callback    (Web)  — admin consent return
# Both are hardcoded off window.location.origin in lib/msal-config.ts.
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-entra-app-client-id
AZURE_AD_CLIENT_SECRET=your-entra-client-secret

# Shared secret for the Windows packager. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
PACKAGER_API_KEY=generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32

# DO NOT add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL / NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY here.
# Their absence is what keeps the catalog on the public snapshot and tokens local
# (the catalog source is chosen by isSupabaseConfigured(), not by DATABASE_MODE).

# ---- Catalog snapshot source (OPTIONAL overrides) ----
# The read-only catalog defaults to downloading upstream's GitHub `catalog-latest`
# release, which upstream FROZE on 2026-07-10 (see DESIGN.md §5). Set one of these to
# point at a snapshot you control instead. These are optional overrides; leave them
# unset to use the (frozen) upstream default. If you set them, they belong in the
# `environment:` block of docker-compose.yml, not necessarily here — CATALOG_SNAPSHOT_BASE_URL
# is the only one that carries a secret-free value worth templating.
#
# CATALOG_SNAPSHOT_BASE_URL=https://github.com/<you>/IntuneGet/releases/download/catalog-latest
# CATALOG_SNAPSHOT_FILE=/data/catalog.sqlite   # explicit local .sqlite; skips all networking
# CATALOG_SNAPSHOT_DIR=/data                    # where the unpacked catalog.sqlite lives
